history.content: Hi! I'm in a similar boat as you, trying to change from BioE to EECS and I just had an appointment with my advisor yesterday. If you're done with EECS16AB, then you can submit the form now. If not, he said they'll be processed after grades for this semester are available and can take about 1-2 weeks to finish processing. I believe Phase 2 starts in August (at least for me), so there should be plenty of time to get the change of major processed before it starts!

I'm an incoming sophomore intending to switch majors from BioE to EECS, and will probably make it well over the GPA cutoff to change majors. However, I am concerned about enrollment.  When are change of major forms processed? I'm currently unable to even enroll on the waitlist for CS 170! Is there any chance the change of major forms will be processed before Phase 2? 

Thanks!
history.subject: EECS Change of Major timeline
